cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification (ReID) using deep neural networks, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various training tricks and techniques to improve the performance of the model, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and evaluates the model on a large dataset, which are common topics in multimedia (cs.MM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
